-- HSBC Names Keir Head of HSBC U.K. Bank Unit, Replacing Robertson
-- B y   G a v i n   F i n c h
-- 2013-07-08T13:35:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-08/hsbc-names-keir-head-of-hsbc-u-k-bank-unit-replacing-robertson.html
HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA) , Europe’s largest
lender, named Alan Keir chief executive officer of HSBC Bank
Plc, overseeing its U.K., European, Middle Eastern and African
divisions.  He replaces Brian Robertson, 59, who is retiring, and will
report to CEO  Stuart Gulliver , the London-based lender said in a
statement today.  Keir, 54, will be replaced as head of HSBC’s global
commercial banking unit by Simon Cooper, 45. Mohammad Al
Tuwaijri will become CEO of HSBC Middle East and North Africa
from October to replace Cooper, the bank said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Gavin Finch in London at 
